00:06:01.896 --> 00:06:03.146 A:middle
for and what they need.

00:06:03.676 --> 00:06:05.766 A:middle
Now this can often be
one of the hardest steps,

00:06:06.316 --> 00:06:09.396 A:middle
because it's not uncommon
for people on the same team

00:06:09.396 --> 00:06:12.466 A:middle
to have completely
different ideas in their mind

00:06:12.466 --> 00:06:14.906 A:middle
about who is going
to be using your app.

00:06:15.516 --> 00:06:18.256 A:middle
But without a shared
understanding

00:06:18.756 --> 00:06:23.366 A:middle
of who your user is, and what
their goals are you might end

00:06:23.366 --> 00:06:27.066 A:middle
up with a hodgepodge of features
that nobody needs, or worse,

00:06:27.066 --> 00:06:29.316 A:middle
you might spend a lot of time
and effort building an app

00:06:30.006 --> 00:06:33.196 A:middle
that nobody knows about because
you targeted the wrong audience.

00:06:33.926 --> 00:06:36.266 A:middle
So let's start with a
couple of simple tips.

00:06:36.266 --> 00:06:38.556 A:middle
First, you are not the user.

00:06:38.736 --> 00:06:43.576 A:middle
You might be a user of your app,
but if you design for yourself,

00:06:43.986 --> 00:06:46.346 A:middle
you risk building in
preconceptions and biases

00:06:46.736 --> 00:06:47.626 A:middle
about the user experience

00:06:47.626 --> 00:06:49.946 A:middle
that might be completely
wrong for everyone else.

00:06:50.826 --> 00:06:54.386 A:middle
For example, I'm an Apple
employee and I'll be a user

00:06:54.386 --> 00:06:56.406 A:middle
of the Caffé Macs app
that we're going to design,

00:06:56.936 --> 00:06:59.486 A:middle
but I almost exclusively
eat cheeseburgers.

00:07:00.086 --> 00:07:03.836 A:middle
And if I were to design the
app for my interest alone,

00:07:03.836 --> 00:07:06.176 A:middle
I'd put the burger of the
day at the top of the screen,

00:07:06.176 --> 00:07:08.306 A:middle
and that would be it because
that's all I really care about.

00:07:08.306 --> 00:07:13.386 A:middle
And that would be great for me,
but maybe not so much for people

00:07:13.386 --> 00:07:16.996 A:middle
who prefer salad, or who like
fish, or whatever else it is

00:07:16.996 --> 00:07:18.486 A:middle
that normal people eat.

00:07:20.056 --> 00:07:22.256 A:middle
Designing for yourself
distracts you

00:07:22.256 --> 00:07:24.616 A:middle
from what matters
most to everyone else.

00:07:25.696 --> 00:07:27.316 A:middle
But the opposite is also true.

00:07:28.526 --> 00:07:30.516 A:middle
Your audience should
not be everyone,

00:07:30.626 --> 00:07:32.486 A:middle
because this is too
vague, it doesn't allow you

00:07:32.486 --> 00:07:34.896 A:middle
to draw any meaningful
conclusions

00:07:35.116 --> 00:07:38.226 A:middle
about what would be most
important, or most valuable

00:07:38.226 --> 00:07:39.736 A:middle
to the real people
who will use your app.

00:07:40.676 --> 00:07:44.196 A:middle
Instead you need to focus on
the essential characteristics

00:07:44.276 --> 00:07:45.576 A:middle
of your target audience.

00:07:46.496 --> 00:07:48.476 A:middle
And one way to do that is

00:07:48.476 --> 00:07:50.646 A:middle
to image you're interviewing
someone who's going

00:07:50.646 --> 00:07:52.916 A:middle
to use your app to
find out what they like

00:07:52.916 --> 00:07:55.296 A:middle
and what they don't like,
and what they care about.

00:07:56.436 --> 00:08:00.796 A:middle
In our case, we might ask our
customer do they prefer a fresh

00:07:56.436 --> 00:08:00.796 A:middle
In our case, we might ask our
customer do they prefer a fresh

00:08:00.796 --> 00:08:02.616 A:middle
meal, or something
off the shelf?

00:08:02.896 --> 00:08:04.546 A:middle
Do they like to take
a leisurely lunch,

00:08:04.746 --> 00:08:06.416 A:middle
or just grab something
between meetings?

00:08:07.446 --> 00:08:09.246 A:middle
Do they get the same
thing every day?

00:08:09.246 --> 00:08:11.736 A:middle
Or do they like to try
something new and different?

00:08:12.226 --> 00:08:14.496 A:middle
And do they prefer
to eat healthy food?

00:08:14.496 --> 00:08:16.846 A:middle
Or do they just pickup
whatever looks good?

00:08:17.856 --> 00:08:20.676 A:middle
Try to capture a range
of characteristics

00:08:20.976 --> 00:08:22.206 A:middle
in a few questions like these.

00:08:23.526 --> 00:08:29.126 A:middle
And then pick the answers that
best reflect the people you want

00:08:29.156 --> 00:08:30.226 A:middle
to serve with your app.

00:08:31.346 --> 00:08:33.586 A:middle
You can use your instinct
and expertise to do this,

00:08:33.586 --> 00:08:36.106 A:middle
and if you have user
research or marketing data,

00:08:36.106 --> 00:08:37.866 A:middle
you can use that to
inform your choices too.

00:08:39.645 --> 00:08:42.626 A:middle
In our case, it's already pretty
easy to walk down to the Caffé

00:08:42.626 --> 00:08:44.346 A:middle
and get a premade
salad or sandwich.

00:08:44.736 --> 00:08:48.066 A:middle
So, instead, we want to focus
on the people who are looking

00:08:48.066 --> 00:08:52.506 A:middle
for a quick interesting, fresh,
and healthy meal every day.

00:08:53.436 --> 00:08:57.066 A:middle
Once you know the
characteristics

00:08:57.066 --> 00:08:59.156 A:middle
of your customer, you
can rephrase those

00:08:59.156 --> 00:09:00.026 A:middle
as a set of goals.

00:08:59.156 --> 00:09:00.026 A:middle
as a set of goals.

00:09:00.986 --> 00:09:04.916 A:middle
So, our customer goals
are to eat a fresh meal,

00:09:05.416 --> 00:09:06.586 A:middle
eat quickly, or sorry.

00:09:06.586 --> 00:09:09.846 A:middle
Enjoy a fresh meal, eat
quickly, try something new,

00:09:10.066 --> 00:09:11.276 A:middle
and make healthy choices.

00:09:12.086 --> 00:09:13.416 A:middle
Articulating your
audiences' goals

00:09:13.416 --> 00:09:15.296 A:middle
like this will help you focus

00:09:15.296 --> 00:09:17.376 A:middle
on their needs throughout
the design process.

00:09:19.496 --> 00:09:20.506 A:middle
But what about you?

00:09:20.636 --> 00:09:24.366 A:middle
What about your goals as an app
developer, or a product owner?

00:09:25.076 --> 00:09:27.786 A:middle
Maybe you want people to
rely on your app every day.

00:09:27.786 --> 00:09:32.326 A:middle
Or maybe you want it to be a
super fun app to play with.

00:09:32.326 --> 00:09:35.446 A:middle
Or maybe you want it
to be blazing fast.

00:09:35.826 --> 00:09:37.716 A:middle
You want to capture those
characteristics too,

00:09:37.926 --> 00:09:45.026 A:middle
as app goals that describe what
you think your app should be

00:09:45.026 --> 00:09:46.786 A:middle
like, how it should feel

00:09:47.006 --> 00:09:49.596 A:middle
and what makes it
memorable, or unique.

00:09:51.396 --> 00:09:53.436 A:middle
So our app goals might be

00:09:53.436 --> 00:09:56.876 A:middle
to provide a convenient
simple delivery service,

00:09:56.926 --> 00:09:59.966 A:middle
so people don't have to walk
all the way to the café.

00:10:00.046 --> 00:10:02.676 A:middle
We want to highlight
the daily entrees

00:10:02.986 --> 00:10:05.086 A:middle
so customers know
all the great options

00:10:05.086 --> 00:10:05.996 A:middle
that are available to them.

00:10:06.886 --> 00:10:09.676 A:middle
And we want Caffé Macs
diners to be happy, of course,

00:10:09.986 --> 00:10:10.886 A:middle
so they keep coming back.

00:10:10.966 --> 00:10:14.246 A:middle
Now, note that this list
does not include things like,

00:10:14.506 --> 00:10:17.486 A:middle
be profitable, or earn a
great return on investment,

00:10:18.156 --> 00:10:20.976 A:middle
or optimize food costs.

00:10:21.826 --> 00:10:24.636 A:middle
While those are important goals
from a business standpoint,

00:10:25.026 --> 00:10:27.226 A:middle
they don't really provide
any meaningful direction

00:10:27.666 --> 00:10:28.646 A:middle
for the design.

00:10:28.886 --> 00:10:32.976 A:middle
And that's because business
goals describe what you want

00:10:32.976 --> 00:10:35.526 A:middle
to get out of your app
after you release it.

00:10:36.296 --> 00:10:39.396 A:middle
App goals on the other
hand describe the qualities

00:10:39.396 --> 00:10:42.926 A:middle
of experience you want
your users to have.

00:10:43.116 --> 00:10:45.676 A:middle
You need to understand both
types of goals, of course.

00:10:45.676 --> 00:10:49.186 A:middle
But it's your app goals that
will inspire and motivate you

00:10:49.186 --> 00:10:50.986 A:middle
to design and build
a great product.

